When I arrived in a small town in rural Spain being around the children of today is a quotidian experience of poverty and lack, a society where enormous gaps between those who have, and those who do not have are insane.Storiesand Art by Taratibu Youth Association of Tanzania (Taratibu YA Tanzania)

Over 15,000 school students across the globe joined the story submissions for our Creative Dream Journal competition comprising of an online video or short story submission.“What is something that you see in this world and really LOVE and would hate to see disappear?”

What is something you would want to see REMAIN in our world (and you will see it remain – despite set-backs and difficulties)?

Unfortunately, many of the young people we shared this competition with highlighted love,peace , justice, conflict resolution especially in their communities, co existence and their rights as the young generation in their societies and their futures as the worrying issues .

Though the levels of violence and peaceful co existence were high,the levels of hope were even higher.Nearly all participants in the creative dream journal competition understood that conflict is a big issue and solution oriented enough to want to see harmony and peaceful co existence restored in their communities.
